summary: I talk a lot about David Tennant, and I guess my dad thought he was some celebrity close to my age or something, because when I...
body: I talk a lot about David Tennant, and I guess my dad thought he was some celebrity close to my age or something, because when I showed him my “1990s lesbian” post, he was like, “Yeah, if he was even alive then.” And so I explained that that picture was from 1994 and that David Tennant is actually only 3 years younger than him, and I just saw this look on his face of absolute horror.

✧ My ask box is usually off. To get in touch with me, @mention me in a post or post something tagged #silveth. It's OK to message me if I follow you, but don't expect immediate responses. That little message notification balloon often makes me anxious and I have to work up to clicking on it. (ya rly.) I rarely follow back people who follow me without there having been some prior contact between us (not never, but not often). I run off a queue of 3-4 posts a day pretty much 24/7. ✧

✧ I'm 40, cis female, Californian (sitting on Ohlone land), Pagan, fae/sidhe, nerd, library cataloger, ISTJ, Virgo liek woah. Be warned: I am introverted, sarcastic, and not very good at looking like a beautiful, kind, interesting person 'cause, yanno, I am really not one. I am usually known in fandom contexts as shyfoxling. ✧

✧ Expect a lot of David Tennant because he is all the awesome. Other contents include, but are not limited to: mythic stuff, Paganism, Doctor Who, Harry Potter (pro-Snape), Tolkien, other nerdy fandom stuff, trees, the stars, occasional American politics and society, and general silliness. If you want otherkin content, you want my sideblog @arethinn. ✧

title: Campbell icons/bases
body:
I think it’s time to admit to myself that I’m never going to finish this project. I’ve been sitting on a mountain of screenshots for over three years and every time I look at the folder sitting on my desktop I just quail at the amount of work and my lack of skill/talent. So here is a ~5 MB .zip file containing 55 “finished” icons and up to 193 potential bases (there may be some duplication of those; I combined things from a few folders).

summary: Do we know what is going on in this scene? I can’t think on the top of my hat what it could be from the book so possibly...
caption:
Do we know what is going on in this scene? I can’t think on the top of my hat what it could be from the book so possibly something new?

By the picture in the background and the shape of the dark tall figure both gifs are from one scene.

In the first one Crowley has his hands tied and is approaching some kind of… altar? In the second one he is turning to see it - I think that the second gif happens before the first one, and it’s that ‘oh shit’ moment for Crowley. By the haircut and the glasses it is not in the past.

That got me thinking. We know that in 1943 Aziraphale tries to be clever which gets him into trouble with the Nazis and Crowley having to save him in a church, and I though it would be really neat if this would be a parallel - Crowley getting into trouble and Aziraphale having to go in some kind of demonic place to save him. :)
